## Why This Is Asked

This question tests practical skills in adding governance to ML deployments within a VPC environment using SageMaker Clarify, while implementing safe rollback mechanisms for bias and drift detection.

## Key Concepts

- **SageMaker Clarify bias checks**: Built-in fairness metrics including disparate impact, conditional demographic disparity, and column-wise bias
- **Drift monitoring**: Feature distribution shift detection comparing current inference traffic against baseline
- **Automated rollback**: Integration with SageMaker Model Registry for version control and automatic deployment rollback
- **PrivateLink/VPC constraints**: Ensuring all monitoring stays within the VPC without external API calls

## Code Example

```javascript
// Pseudo-code: compute DI and drift, then trigger rollback if thresholds exceeded
function evaluateModel(inputs, protectedAttrs, baseline) {
  const bias = computeDisparateImpact(inputs, protectedAttrs);
  const drift = computeFeatureDrift(inputs, baseline);

  if (bias < 0.8 || drift > 0.3) {
    triggerAutomaticRollback();
    sendAlert({ bias, drift, status: 'rollback_triggered' });
  }

  return { bias, drift, healthy: true };
}
```

## Implementation Approach

**(a) Data Sampling**: Sample 5,000 inference requests over a sliding window (e.g., last 24 hours), ensuring representation of protected attributes. Store samples in S3 within the VPC for Clarify processing.

**(b) Threshold Configuration**: Set disparate impact threshold at 0.8 (industry standard for 80% rule) and feature drift threshold at 0.3. When exceeded, invoke Lambda to trigger SageMaker endpoint configuration rollback.

**(c) Minimal Dashboard**: Deploy a lightweight CloudWatch dashboard showing real-time DI score, drift score, and rollback status with simple threshold breach alerts.

